   "source": [
    "This chart above now reveals that users who took the most steps also get most sleep.\n",
    "\n",
    "Users looking to maintain a desirable level of physical health will be interested in setting goals for their physical activities. Smart devices are culturally known as a tool for this; therefore, users may have been looking towards the well-known (Gordon, Althoff, and Leskovec, 2019) 10,000-steps-a-day goal. With little to no scientific evidence for the 10,000 steps goal, the 7,500 steps threshold may be adopted to evaluate users' steps as the study of I-Min Lee, et.al., 2019 suggested that 7,500 was the point at which, additional steps per day did not progressively improve mortality rates.  \n",
    "\n",
    "So, were users taking as many steps as 7,500 per day during the week? \n",
    "\n",
    "From the next Chart, we can confirm that,\n",
    "\n",
    "•\tThey did on every day except Sunday.\n",
    "\n",
    "•\tUsers don't sleep the recommended amount of minutes/ hours - 8 hours.\n",
    "\n",
    "•\tUsers are most active on Saturday.\n",
    "\n"
   ]
